There shouldn't be a comma after the word dear in a greeting.
comma逗号（，）。
In a date, commas should appear both before and after the year.
comma逗号（，）。
Some of the words of the phrase Department of State should start with uppercase.
uppercase大写字母
The verb be must agree in number and person with its subject.
题目，问题；主题；对象 (语法)主语 
I've said all there is to be said on the subject.
关于这个问题我要说的都说完了。题目，问题；主题；对象 (语法)主语 
he's the subject of a major new biography.
他是一部重要新传记的主人公。题目，问题；主题；对象 (语法)主语 
The preposition "about" must be replaced with the preposition "for" in the phrase "search for somebody".
search for somebody
The verb need must be followed by the infinitive or the gerund of the verb get.
need to do...gerund(语法)动名词 need doing...
This sentence is missing a dot.
括号中的句子最后的点掉了也是语法错误。
This noun is missing a determiner before it.
determiner限定词，限定成分，（如a, the, every）
There should be a comma between a long prepositional phrase and the main clause.
prepositional前置词，介词
This auxiliary is missing a verb.
auxiliary(语法)助动词 辅助的 
an auxiliary nurse.
助理护士，护理员。
auxiliary airport staff.
机场辅助人员。
the ship has an auxiliary power source.
这艘船有辅助发电设备。
The pronoun which should be used because the subject My business refers to a non-human.

The verb offer must agree in number and person with its subject My business.
offers~~~
The subject pronoun they is mistaken for the object them.
subject(语法)主语 题目，问题；主题；对象 object(语法)宾语 对象；目标 
There should not be any space before the punctuation ending a sentence.
punctuation标点（符号后加空格，但前面不行。）
Compound modifiers containing numbers are hyphenated before nouns when the compound contains a period of time, a unit of measurement or a currency.
hyphenated用连字号连接的modifier(语法)修饰语
In this context, this public place noun should start with uppercase.
uppercase大写字母
The number thousands must be followed by the preposition of.
thousands of ...
The noun sport must at plural form in the compound noun sports car.
this grammar check website is quite powerful...
The expression "some of" implies the nominal group must have the determiner "the".
nominal(语法)名词的 
The verb be must agree in number and person with its subject Each.
Each of your employees...
After plural nouns ending with s, the genitive must have only an apostrophe.
employees's(X)genitive属格的，所有格的  apostrophe撇号（即 ’）(修辞)呼语法
The symbol $ represented by the currency dollar must be placed before the number.
$1234... 
There should not be any space between an opening quotation mark and the word starting the quote.
quotation引文，引语，语录 quote引号
Periods always go inside quotation marks.
Periods时期, 节段, 节, 句点, 学时, 周期 （句号在引号内）
There should be a comma after an introductory adverbial element.
introductory引导的，引论的，序言的；基本的，基础的，初步的，预备的adverbial副词的，状语的(afterward, we)
an introductory course in Russian.
俄语基础教程。
Everyday is an adjective, It should be replaced by the adverb every day.
do something everyday...
A comma shouldn’t directly separate a verb and its subject.

In this context, the verb say should be replaced by the verb tell, We say something and we tell someone something.

After a preposition, a verb must in the gerund form.
gerund(语法)动名词
The verb give shouldn’t have preposition after it, The expression is give someone something.
(Or give something to someone.)
Interrogative sentences should end with a question mark. 
Interrogative疑问的；讯问的；好问的 
Two independent clauses shouldn't be joined only by a comma, avoid comma splices.
splice接合, 胶接, 结婚
If the tense of a verb of a conditional clause is present, the tense of the verb of the main clause should be present or future.
