The article "a" must be replaced with the article "the" before an ordinal number written in digit.
ordinal（与）顺序（有关）的 digit(0到9的任一）数字；数位，位
The preposition "at" should be used if the following nouns denote an hour or specific time of day, or a celebration. 
denote表示，指示 
The preposition on should be used if the following nouns denote a day of week, a date, or days of celebration.

The adverb eagerly shouldn't be between a verb and its direct object.
eagerly热切的 渴望的
There shouldn't be the preposition to between a modal and a verb.
modal(语法)语气的 (would)
If it is in case of a letter or an e-mail, a comma should be used after the closing of a friendly or business letter.
Kind Regards, 
In a "he said/she said" clause, commas always go before the quotation marks.
